<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
OK.. I wanted to start a topic that addresses the concern of out pets being very vulnerable in raid situations, instead of addressing it in unrelated topics.<P>As for fear and riposte being a prime concern.  Mages and Necro's have pet immune fear, bst might get it however that still leaves open the door or riposte, which are equally deadly.  I can't see BST having both protections without the mage's and necro's crying for it as well.  I also honestly don't see VI giving all pet classes buff spells that make the pets supermen either.  <P>So in exchange for NOT getting immune fear for the pet, lets have the BST pet get "Spirit of Vapors" Since Fear is a spell ability by mobs and riposte is a physical melee ability let the BST pet become "vapor".  This would still allow the pets to get hit by melee and spells, however it would decrease the amount of the hit to not exceed a certain level. Maybe capping it so that riposte end up not doing anymore damage then a marginal bash of a couple or few hundred hitpoints at most. ?????<P>Just a thought..   This way mage's/necro's have fear and we get riposte protection.. one being a trade off vs. the others.
</FONT>
