Here is another idea about riposte.<P>What happens when you punch a brick wall? Do you has a person take damage?  OUCH, you bet you do. So that being the case why not trade back that damage to the originator.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>New 59th Pet Spell.. Spirit of Granite.. once this spell is casted about your pet it allows him to identify that a surprise risoste is comming at the last minute and your Spirit Warder is instantly able to turn into Granite returning TWICE the damage he took.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  <P>Mob_01 riposte warder for 800 damage.<BR>Mob_01 takes 1600 damage from non-melee damage.<P>Yes.. granted that pets will die just as quick, but oh boy will they be able to dish out some damage before buying the farm  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>hahaha I can see it now.. <P>/guild OK all Beastlords buff your pets and lets hope they mobs riposte the crap out of them.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Well maybe a 2 to 1 ratio is a bit much  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">, but I can dream.  However, maybe a equal return in damage is more in line.  This way the amount of time that is lost in the BST in recasting his dead pet and buffing it compenstated with the equal damage that pet did when it took the riposte.
