How about they implement a feature where - in the middle of a fight - you go and stand behind the monster about 20 or 30 feet - then command your pet to stop attacking and come over to you - then you command the pet to attack again and it moves in a straight line to the mob.  Seems like an easy idea to me.<BR>On the other hand a pet immune to fear sounds also like a good idea - what if the fearless discipline also affected the pet at the same time ?<BR>I dont like the idea of pets being unripostable - it just allows lazy players to add pet damage to a mob without having to make any effort to control the pet.  Heck as a SK all I had to do was build up agro (SK can do that easy enough) then take baby steps away from the mob so it follows, until all the pets were behind the mob (a chanter pet, a mage pet and my own lil skelly) - no riposte - additedly I am not lvl 60 tanking ubers - I dont care.  And this way - the poor old enchanter pet wasnt getting riposted, so super pet control still wasnt needed.<BR>On the other hand, if your pet has agro - well, it is going to get munched by far worse than the ripostes, so I cant really see how any sensible player has a problem - if your pet hasnt got agro and your tank isnt some clown who goes spinning around the mob, it should be easy to minimise thr ripostes.<BR>If the rogue occasionally gains agro and the monster spins, well, so be it.  If the tanks keep dropping like flies and the mob keeps spining to get the next one, well, you got more problems than ripostes anyway.
