Having never gotten to high levels for raiding or had a high level pet... I'm just wondering what the problem with riposte is?<P>Pet immune to riposte doesn't sound good to me. I've heard high level mobs become enraged and riposte every attack. I don't see how you could allow an army of pets to attack an enraged mob with no penalty.<P>Is it too hard to keep your pet at the back side of a high level mob in a prolonged fight?  What is the problem with your pet occassionally being riposted to death if the mob turns around?  Will recasting a low level pet automatically aggro all uber mobs in the area or something?  It seems that if you have Clarity or C2, the cost of recasting and rebuffing a pet is almost nill, since BL pets don't even require material components. Is a fight won or lost in the time it takes to buff a pet?<P>As for the immunity to fear thing, that sounds like a valid question... Maybe just give us a rare drop pet buff spell with short duration and long recast time that buffs our pet against fear. Equivalent of the fearless disc or something. That sounds like it would be in line with what we have already.<P>Sorry for rambling... It'll be a long time before I have to worry about these issues in game.
