<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The issue is that pets are all-but-impossible to re-position on another side of a MOB once battle is joined. Re-casting a pet and buffing it is not so much a mana issue as a time issue. That is almost half a minute where you&#8217;re not doing any damage to the MOB at all. Having to re-summon a pet 3 or 4 times in a long raid encounter wouldn&#8217;t be worth it because of the melee damage lost from you for the time spent summoning/buffing.<P>The Ripostes on these mobs can be over 1,000. On the MOBs that hit this hard there would be no damage of massed pet attacks working because the MOB would chew through a pet every single round or every other round with double, triple, and quad attacks. During an extended battle, 2 or 3 ripostes will kill the pet and you are definitely going to get that number fairly quickly.<P>Immunity may not be the best way to handle it. A better tool/command for positioning pets would be better but I&#8217;m not sure either is doable.<P>--------------------<P>Balance doesn&#8217;t always mean you getting more and/or others getting less. Sometimes you have to recognize that you should be the one to not get more, or to give something up.
