Very well written RR.<P>Pets are expendable mini tanks, plain and simple. You don't want your pet getting pounded to death from mobs, then have that cleric use is almighty shield buffs to buff the pets to the max, like he would a primary tank.  Sounds to me is that you expect pets to be just as livable as tanks without the cost.  If the Buffers of the raid don't want to buff the pets to max then don't go whining to VI that your pets die to quickly from mob hits.  I'm sure that is you use all the shield buffs allowed on your pets there is no reason why you can't use some of that stingy mana on healing them when they do take a riposte..<P>Like my mama always use to tell me. "Taking a pet into a Raid is like a box of chocolates, you never know what you're going to get"   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>PS.. Here is a clue Mr Sshadow Lazy man.. I hate to inform you how to control your pet, but I see now I have to clue you in on how a TRUE experience player does it.<P>Make a HOTKEY  /pet guard me<BR>Make a HOTKEY  /pet back off<BR>Make a HOTKEY  /pet attack<BR>Make a HOTKEY  /pet guard here<P>Using those 4 primary commands will most of the time keep your pet to the back of the mob.  HOW SO?  First of you make sure that YOU don't fight the MOB head on either. As long as YOU always position yourself to the MOB's back, you have a great chance in using the above commands in keeping the pet by your side fighting the mob from it's backside or side...  If you are too lazy to use any other HOTKEYS besides attack and kick then you need to play another class..<P>The skill of commanding your pet is an art just as a monk pulling for the group.  NOT all monks are good and not all casters are good at controlling their pets. (looking @ you)  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  I honestly don't think VI should compensate a poor pet casters from riposte.
