<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>The only way anyone can even tank them is a warrior with defensive discipline. We dont want our pets to tank in these situations (which is fortunate because they dont have defensive and so cant do it, at all) we want them to be damage dealers  <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>OK.. you want them to be DAMAGE DEALERS, but you don't want to take the trade off that they might die in the process. This is funny actually.. YOU WANT pets to dish out the damage but NOT die.... That is like a caster that cast a spell and gets it resisted.  That is part of the game. You may hit for full damage, partial or NONE at all.  Use this in your thinking if your mind can grasp such a concept:<P>PET = Damage Spell<P>It may get resisted (hence pet dies quickly)<BR>It may only hit for partial damage (hence pet tanks a bit then dies)<BR>It may hit for full damage (hence the pet lives for most of the fight if not all of it)<P>PET+BUFFS=MANA<P>It's really not that hard of a formula to understand, so rather you want to call it a pet or casting a damage spell.. YOU may fizzle, YOU may get resisted or YOU might actually hit for damage.   What you are wanting with immune riposte is like a caster wanting "NON RESISTABLE" damage spells..
