<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Yes, all the non-tank players (especially the Rogues) normally try to stay behind the MOB and thus have no issue with Riposte.<P>Monks, Rangers, Rogues, Non-Tank-List Warriors, Shadow Knights, Paladins, and Meleeing Bards (I wonder if I left anyone out?) cannot take repeated ripostes any better than our pets can. Back-up healers in individual groups may be able to keep up with a single one but if there are multiple ripostes these classes will drop very quickly also. Hence the need for our pet, like other non-tank melees, to stay behind the mob. To think of a pet as a "tank" in any kind of meaningful high-end raid is silly. They can't take that kind of damage at that kind of rate. They are damage dealers in these situations. <P>If the above simple hot keys worked well, it wouldn't be a problem. They don't.<P>--------------------<P>Balance doesn&#8217;t always mean you getting more and/or others getting less. Sometimes you have to recognize that you should be the one to not get more, or to give something up.
</FONT>
