I just thought of something:<P>Everyone knows that the random number generator for EQ is kind of screwy, right?  It seems to generate hideous clusters of numbers.  <P>(This is from memory so take it with a grain of salt)  Most rolls that I've seen either cluster around 30 or around 90. Likewise people usually riposte/dodge/block crit/crip/proc in long strings, right?<P>  So how feasible would it be to hit /pet back off when the mob ripostes, then wait a second or two to sic 'em again?  Likewise for tanks actually attacking the mob, when you see a riposte, you click off auto-attack for a second or two, then start in again?  Would the damage output outweigh the damage avoided by not attacking?  Would the loss of taunt cause the MT to lose aggro?  Like I said, it's just a thought  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">.
