Riposte is based on a skill check, where the MUD . err EQ server  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  generates a random number and checks it against the skill (mob or player). I'm not sure, how EQ's RNG is coded, but most number generators use a time function in the generation, so the riposte would almost definitely 'wear itself out'  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
