OH come on.. You all act like every single pet dies in 5 seconds and it's just a waste.  I think if you watch G's post from his 60th level exp, you'll see that he doesn't indicate that his pet is dying so quickly as SOME would like people to belief.  I've seen the "stats" of the class damage outputs during raids and it looks like most do just fine 75%? of the time.<P>Have you ever thought that maybe, just maybe that the reason why some pets get ripostle more then others at times is becaues of the HATE list order, where the #1 person on the hate list will recieve a higher chance of ripostle then others.. so on and so on... Try doing a study on that with pets with those that use "taunt on" and "taunt off".. I would bet you that you'll fine more pets getting ripostle with taunt then those without.<P>If your pet gets a riposte, then back him off for a bit.   If your pet is recieving more then 1 or 2 ripostle quickly (given all the tanks that are in proxemity) the chance are your pet has gained too much attention and you need to turn "taunt" OFF.. <P>Give it a shot  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
